00126 int
00127 get_int_parm (MD * md, char *parm_name)
00128 {
00129   MD_Field *value_field;
00130   char *value_string, *ptr, *end_ptr;
00131   int value;
00132 
00133   value_field = find_parm_value (md, parm_name);
00134   value_string = MD_get_string (value_field, 0);
00135 
00136   /* Convert string to int */
00137 
00138   /* Require the int to have at least 1 digit in it */
00139   for (ptr = value_string; *ptr != 0; ptr++)
00140     {
00141       if (isdigit (*ptr))
00142         break;
00143     }
00144   if (*ptr == 0)
00145     I_punt ("Parm '%s': invalid int value '%s'\n", value_string);
00146 
00147   /* Convert to long, make sure
00148    * conversion goes to end of string.
00149    */
00150   value = (int) strtol (value_string, &end_ptr, 0);
00151 
00152   if (*end_ptr != 0)
00153     I_punt ("Parm '%s': invalid int value '%s'\n", value_string);
00154 
00155   return (value);
00156 }
00157 /* Returns 1 s1 matches s2 (ignoring case), 0 otherwise */
00158 static int
00159 value_match (char *s1, char *s2)
00160 {
00161   for (; *s1 != 0; s1++, s2++)
00162     {
00163       if (toupper (*s1) != toupper (*s2))
00164         return (0);
00165     }
00166 
00167   if (*s2 != 0)
00168     return (0);
00169   else
00170     return (1);
00171 }

00173 /* Returns 1 or 0 depending on parm value.
00174  * The following are equivalent (yes, y, 1, on) (no, n, 0, off).
00175  */
00176 int
00177 get_binary_parm (MD * md, char *parm_name)
00178 {
00179   MD_Field *value_field;
00180   char *value_string;
00181 
00182   value_field = find_parm_value (md, parm_name);
00183   value_string = MD_get_string (value_field, 0);
00184 
00185   /* Convert to binary value */
00186   if (value_match (value_string, "yes") ||
00187       value_match (value_string, "y") ||
00188       value_match (value_string, "1") || value_match (value_string, "on"))
00189     return (1);
00190 
00191   if (value_match (value_string, "no") ||
00192       value_match (value_string, "n") ||
00193       value_match (value_string, "0") || value_match (value_string, "off"))
00194     return (0);
00195 
00196   I_punt ("Parm '%s': invalid binary value '%s'\n", parm_name, value_string);
00197 
00198   return (0);                   /* To make the compiler happy */
00199 }

00269 void
00270 set_latencies (MD_Entry * entry, char *field_name, int *lat_array)
00271 {
00272   MD_Entry *lat_entry;
00273   MD_Field *field, *time_field;
00274   int index1, lat;
00275 
00276   /* Do nothing if field not set */
00277   if ((field = find_field_by_name (entry, field_name)) == NULL)
00278     return;
00279 
00280   for (index1 = 0; index1 <= field->max_element_index; index1++)
00281     {
00282       lat_entry = MD_get_link (field, index1);
00283       if ((time_field = find_field_by_name (lat_entry, "time")) == NULL)
00284         I_punt ("set_latencies: %s->%s[%i]->%s time field expected!",
00285                 entry->name, field_name, index1, lat_entry->name);
00286 
00287       /* First time is latency */
00288       lat = MD_get_int (time_field, 0);
00289       lat_array[index1] = lat;
00290 
00291       /* Sanity check */
00292       if (time_field->max_element_index != 0)
00293         I_punt ("set_latencies: %s->%s only one time may be specified!",
00294                 time_field->entry->section->name, time_field->entry->name);
00295     }
00296 }

00299 calc_num_op_alts (MD_Entry * impact_op_entry)
00300 {
00301   MD_Entry *op_entry, *alt_entry;
00302   MD_Field *op_field, *alt_field, *format_field;
00303   int num_alts;
00304   int index1, index2;
00305 
00306   num_alts = 0;
00307 
00308   /* Get the op field */
00309   op_field = find_field_by_name (impact_op_entry, "op");
00310 
00311   /* Sum up for each of this impact_op's operations */
00312   for (index1 = 0; index1 <= op_field->max_element_index; index1++)
00313     {
00314       /* Get the op entry */
00315       op_entry = MD_get_link (op_field, index1);
00316 
00317       /* Get the alt field */
00318       alt_field = find_field_by_name (op_entry, "alt");
00319 
00320       /* Sum up all the IO formats (each will be a different alt) for
00321        * each alternative.
00322        */
00323       for (index2 = 0; index2 <= alt_field->max_element_index; index2++)
00324         {
00325           alt_entry = MD_get_link (alt_field, index2);
00326 
00327           format_field = find_field_by_name (alt_entry, "format");
00328 
00329           num_alts += format_field->max_element_index + 1;
00330         }
00331     }
00332

00449 Mdes *
00450 load_lmdes_from_version2 (char *file_name, int num_pred, int num_dest,
00451                           int num_src, int num_sync)
00452 {
00453   MD *md;
00454   Mdes *mdes;
00455   char *processor_model;
00456   int struct_size;
00457   int data_size;
00458   int set_table_size;
00459   int alt_size;
00460   int buf_size;
00461   int *mask_ptr;
00462   int *array_ptr;
00463   Mdes_IO_Set **type_ptr;
00464   Mdes_Alt *alt_ptr;
00465   int total_string_len;
00466   int total_alts;
00467   Mdes_IO_Set *IO_set;
00468   Mdes_IO_Item *IO_item;
00469   Mdes_Resource *resource;
00470   Mdes_Latency *latency;
00471   Mdes_Alt *alt;
00472   Mdes_Operation *operation;
00473   char *name_buf_ptr;
00474   int IO_item_id, reslist_id, latency_id;
00475   int i, j;
00476   /* MD parsing local variables */
00477   Mdes_IO_Set *null_IO_set;
00478   MD_Section *section;
00479   MD_Entry *entry;
00480   MD_Field *field;
00481   int index1;
00482   /* 20031024 SZU */
00483   int num_slots, slots_per_template, max_template_per_issue;
00484   SM_Nop *first_nop = NULL, *last_nop = NULL, *current_nop = NULL;
00485   int num_nop = 0;
00486   int *nop_array;
00487 
00488   /* Malloc mdes structure and copy file name to field */
00489   Malloc_struct ((void **) &mdes, sizeof (Mdes));
00490   Malloc_name (&mdes->file_name, file_name);
00491 
00492   mdes->mdes2 = load_mdes2 (file_name);
00493 
00494   /* Read the md version of the machine description */
00495   md = mdes->mdes2->md_mdes;
00496 
00497   /* Point the mdes2 version of the mdes at the version1 version */
00498   mdes->mdes2->version1_mdes = mdes;
00499 
00500   /* Get the processor model */
00501   processor_model = get_string_parm (md, "processor_model");
00502 
00503 #if DEBUG_LMDES2
00504   printf ("Processor model is '%s'\n", processor_model);
00505 #endif
00506 
00507   if (strcmp (processor_model, "superscalar") == 0)
00508     mdes->processor_model = MDES_SUPERSCALAR;
00509   else if (strcmp (processor_model, "vliw") == 0)
00510     mdes->processor_model = MDES_VLIW;
00511   else
00512     I_punt ("load_lmdes_from_version2:\n"
00513             " processor model expected to be superscalar or vliw not '%s'",
00514             processor_model);
00515 
00516 
00517   mdes->number[MDES_PRED] = get_int_parm (md, "num_pred_operands");
00518   mdes->number[MDES_DEST] = get_int_parm (md, "num_dest_operands");
00519   mdes->number[MDES_SRC] = get_int_parm (md, "num_src_operands");
00520 
00521   /* Version2 currently allows 3 syncs to be specified */
00522   mdes->number[MDES_SYNC_IN] = 3;
00523   mdes->number[MDES_SYNC_OUT] = 3;
00524 
00525   /* Increase operand counts to be at least as big as those specified
00526    * by the parameters. This allows guarantees the mdes operand counts 
00527    * will be compatable with the lcode operand counts, etc.
00528    */
00529   if (mdes->number[MDES_PRED] < num_pred)
00530     mdes->number[MDES_PRED] = num_pred;
00531   if (mdes->number[MDES_DEST] < num_dest)
00532     mdes->number[MDES_DEST] = num_dest;
00533   if (mdes->number[MDES_SRC] < num_src)
00534     mdes->number[MDES_SRC] = num_src;
00535   if (mdes->number[MDES_SYNC_IN] < num_sync)
00536     mdes->number[MDES_SYNC_IN] = num_sync;
00537   if (mdes->number[MDES_SYNC_OUT] < num_sync)
00538     mdes->number[MDES_SYNC_OUT] = num_sync;
00539 
00540 
00541   /* Get the slot statisitics */
00542   mdes->max_slot = get_int_parm (md, "max_slot");
00543   mdes->num_slots = get_int_parm (md, "num_slots");
00544 
00545   /* Currently, max_slot better be num_slots -1 */
00546   if (mdes->max_slot != (mdes->num_slots - 1))
00547     I_punt ("load_lmdes_from_version2:\n"
00548             "max_slot (%i) expected to be num_slots (%i) -1!",
00549             mdes->max_slot, mdes->num_slots);
00550 
00551 #if DEBUG_LMDES2
00552   printf ("Number: pred %i dest %i src %i max_slot %i num_slots %i\n",
00553           mdes->number[MDES_PRED], mdes->number[MDES_DEST],
00554           mdes->number[MDES_SRC], mdes->max_slot, mdes->num_slots);
00555 #endif
00556 
00557   /* 20030601 SZU
00558    * Itanium checks.
00559    * Check that slots_per_template <= num_slots.
00560    * Check that num_slots % slots_per_template = 0.
00561    * Check that slots_per_template * max_template_per_issue <= num_slots
00562    */
00563   num_slots = mdes->num_slots;
00564   slots_per_template = mdes->mdes2->sm_mdes->slots_per_template;
00565   max_template_per_issue = mdes->mdes2->sm_mdes->max_template_per_issue;
00566 
00567 #if DEBUG_LMDES2
00568   printf ("slots_per_template %i max_template_per_issue %i\n",
00569           slots_per_template, max_template_per_issue);
00570 #endif
00571 
00572   if (slots_per_template != 0)
00573     if ((slots_per_template > num_slots) ||
00574         (num_slots % slots_per_template != 0) ||
00575         (slots_per_template * max_template_per_issue > num_slots))
00576       I_punt ("load_lmdes_from_version2: Something wrong w/ relationship betw:"
00577               "\nnum_slots %i slots_per_template %i max_template_per_issue %i",
00578               num_slots, slots_per_template, max_template_per_issue);
00579 
00580   /*
00581    * Get total operand count, latency count, and calculate offsets into

01181               current_nop->next_nop = NULL;

01185                 {
01186                   first_nop = current_nop;
01187                   last_nop = current_nop;
01188                 }
01189               else
01190                 {
01191                   last_nop->next_nop = current_nop;
01192                   current_nop->prev_nop = last_nop;
01193                   last_nop = current_nop;
01194                 }
01195 #if DEBUG_LMDES2
01196               printf ("Operation %s is a nop: priority %i opcode %i\n",
01197                       operation->external_name, current_nop->priority,
01198                       current_nop->opcode);
01199 #endif
01200             }
01201           else
01202             {
01203               operation->nop = 0;
01204             }
01205         }
01206       else
01207         {
01208           operation->nop = 0;
01209         }
01210 
01211       /* 20020805 SZU
01212        * Added to keep track of latency classes.
01213        * Should be done only if Prod_Cons_Latency exist
01214        */
01215       if (MD_find_field_decl (entry->section, "lat_class") != NULL)
01216         {

01273

01307                   name_buf_ptr += strlen (alt->asm_name) + 1;

01310                   j++;

01313         }
01314

01316       alt_ptr += operation->num_alts;
01317 
01318       /* Go to next IMPACT_Operation entry */
01319       entry = MD_next_entry (entry);
01320     }
01321 
01322   /* 20030603 SZU
01323    * Make nop array w/ nop linked list structure
01324    */
01325   if (num_nop > 0)
01326     {
01327       mdes->mdes2->sm_mdes->max_nop_index = num_nop - 1;
01328 
01329       if ((nop_array = (int *) malloc (num_nop * sizeof (int))) == NULL)
01330         I_punt ("load_lmdes_from_version2: Out of memory");
01331 
01332       for (i = 0; i < num_nop; i++)
01333         nop_array[i] = -1;
01334 
01335       for (current_nop = first_nop; current_nop != NULL;
01336            current_nop = current_nop->next_nop)
01337         nop_array[current_nop->priority] = current_nop->opcode;
01338 
01339 #if DEBUG_LMDES2
01340       printf ("Printing nop_array: num_nop %i\n", num_nop);
01341       for (i = 0; i < num_nop; i++)

01343 #endif
01344 
01345       /* Sanity check */
01346       for (i = 0; i < num_nop; i++)
01347         if (nop_array[i] < 0)
01348           I_punt ("load_lmdes_from_version2: bad nop specifications!");
01349 
01350       mdes->mdes2->sm_mdes->nop_array = nop_array;
01351     }
01352   else
01353     {
01354       /* No NOP specified */
01355       mdes->mdes2->sm_mdes->nop_array = NULL;
01356     }
01357 
01358   /* Allocate temporary buffers used by Mdes routines */
01359   buf_size = mdes->operand_count * sizeof (Mdes_IO_Set *);
01360   Malloc_struct ((void **) &mdes->operand_type_buf, buf_size);
01361 
01362   /* Get MDES2 specific parms.  See header file for description
01363    * of these parameters.
01364    */
01365   mdes->check_resources_for_only_one_alt =
01366     get_binary_parm (md, "check_resources_for_only_one_alt");
01367 
01368   return (mdes);
01369 }

01467 void
01468 print_check_history (FILE * out, char *name, char *type,
01469                      INT_Symbol_Table * table)
01470 {
01471   INT_Symbol *symbol;
01472   Heap *heap;
01473   int total_checks;
01474 
01475   total_checks = 0;
01476 
01477   /* Create heap */
01478   heap = Heap_Create (HEAP_MIN);
01479 
01480   for (symbol = table->head_symbol; symbol != NULL;
01481        symbol = symbol->next_symbol)
01482     {
01483       Heap_Insert (heap, (void *) symbol, (double) symbol->value);
01484 #ifdef LP64_ARCHITECTURE
01485       total_checks += (int)((long) symbol->data);
01486 #else
01487       total_checks += (int) symbol->data;
01488 #endif
01489     }
01490 
01491 
01492   fprintf (out, "%s %s check history:\n", name, type);
01493 
01494   /* Return now if history empty */
01495   if (total_checks == 0)
01496     {
01497       fprintf (out, "\n");
01498       return;
01499     }
01500 
01501   while ((symbol = (INT_Symbol *) Heap_ExtractTop (heap)) != NULL)
01502     {
01503 #ifdef LP64_ARCHITECTURE
01504       fprintf (out, "  %4i  %8i  %5.2f%%\n", symbol->value,
01505                (int)((long) symbol->data),
01506                (double) 100.0 * ((double) ((int)((long) symbol->data))) /
01507                ((double) total_checks));
01508 #else
01509       fprintf (out, "  %4i  %8i  %5.2f%%\n", symbol->value,
01510                (int) symbol->data,
01511                (double) 100.0 * ((double) ((int) symbol->data)) /
01512                ((double) total_checks));
01513 #endif
01514     }
01515   fprintf (out, "\n");
01516 }

01525   double checks_per_option;
01526

01528     ((double) do_stats->num_oper_checks);
01529 
01530   /* Count only usage checks, but fails for usage or slot constraints */
01531   total_checks = can_stats->num_usage_checks;
01532   checks_per_op = ((double) total_checks) /
01533     ((double) do_stats->num_oper_checks);
01534   checks_per_try = ((double) total_checks) /
01535     ((double) can_stats->num_oper_checks);
01536   checks_per_option = ((double) total_checks) /
01537     ((double) can_stats->num_option_checks);
01538 
01539   options_per_try = ((double) can_stats->num_option_checks) /
01540     ((double) can_stats->num_oper_checks);
01541 
01542 
01543 
01544   total_checks_failed =
01545     can_stats->num_usage_checks_failed + can_stats->num_slot_checks_failed;
01546   fails_per_op = ((double) total_checks_failed) /
01547     ((double) do_stats->num_oper_checks);
01548   fails_per_try = ((double) total_checks_failed) /
01549     ((double) can_stats->num_oper_checks);
01550 
01551   /* For Micro 29 */
01552   fprintf (out, "%-12s %10i %10.2f %10.2f %10.2f %10.2f\n",
01553            name, do_stats->num_oper_checks,
01554            tries_per_op, options_per_try, checks_per_try, checks_per_option);
01555 /*    
01556     fprintf (out, "%-25s %7i %4.1f %4.1f/%4.1f %4.1f/%4.1f\n",

01558              do_stats->num_oper_checks,
01559              tries_per_op,
01560              checks_per_op, checks_per_try,
01561              fails_per_op, fails_per_try);
01562 */
01563 }

01565 void
01566 print_mdes_stats (FILE * out, int prepass)
01567 {
01568   Mdes_Stats *can_stats, *do_stats;
01569   Mdes_Operation *op;
01570   int opc;
01571   Mdes_Stats total_can_stats, total_do_stats;
01572   Mdes_Stats uncond_can_stats, uncond_do_stats;
01573   Mdes_Stats cbr_can_stats, cbr_do_stats;
01574   Mdes_Stats load_can_stats, load_do_stats;
01575   Mdes_Stats store_can_stats, store_do_stats;
01576   Mdes_Stats other_can_stats, other_do_stats;
01577   int total_checks;
01578   Heap *heap;
01579 
01580   /* Only can print stats for mdes version2! */
01581   if (lmdes->mdes2 == NULL)
01582     {
01583       fprintf (out, "Version 1 mdes, stats not printed\n");
01584       return;
01585     }
01586 
01587   init_stats (&total_can_stats);
01588   init_stats (&total_do_stats);
01589 
01590   init_stats (&uncond_can_stats);
01591   init_stats (&uncond_do_stats);
01592   init_stats (&cbr_can_stats);
01593   init_stats (&cbr_do_stats);
01594   init_stats (&load_can_stats);
01595   init_stats (&load_do_stats);
01596   init_stats (&store_can_stats);
01597   init_stats (&store_do_stats);
01598   init_stats (&other_can_stats);
01599   init_stats (&other_do_stats);
01600 
01601   /* Create heap */
01602   heap = Heap_Create (HEAP_MAX);
01603 
01604   /* Place each non-zero weighted item on heap, sort by total checks */
01605   for (opc = 0; opc <= lmdes->max_opcode; opc++)
01606     {
01607       op = lmdes->op_table[opc];
01608 
01609       /* Skip unused opcodes */
01610       if (op == NULL)
01611         continue;
01612 
01613       /* Skip unexecuted opcodes */
01614       if (prepass)
01615         {
01616           can_stats = &op->can_sched_prepass;
01617           do_stats = &op->sched_prepass;
01618         }
01619       else
01620         {
01621           can_stats = &op->can_sched_postpass;
01622           do_stats = &op->sched_postpass;
01623         }
01624 
01625       if ((can_stats->num_oper_checks == 0) &&
01626           (do_stats->num_oper_checks == 0))
01627         continue;
01628 
01629 
01630       total_checks = can_stats->num_slot_checks + can_stats->num_usage_checks;
01631 
01632       Heap_Insert (heap, (void *) op,
01633                    (double) (total_checks) - ((double) opc / 1000.0));
01634 
01635 
01636       add_stats (&total_can_stats, can_stats);
01637       add_stats (&total_do_stats, do_stats);
01638 
01639       if ((op->op_flags & OP_FLAG_JMP) ||
01640           (op->op_flags & OP_FLAG_RTS) || (op->op_flags & OP_FLAG_JSR))
01641         {
01642           add_stats (&uncond_can_stats, can_stats);
01643           add_stats (&uncond_do_stats, do_stats);
01644         }
01645       else if (op->op_flags & OP_FLAG_CBR)
01646         {
01647           add_stats (&cbr_can_stats, can_stats);
01648           add_stats (&cbr_do_stats, do_stats);
01649         }
01650       else if (op->op_flags & OP_FLAG_LOAD)
01651         {
01652           add_stats (&load_can_stats, can_stats);
01653           add_stats (&load_do_stats, do_stats);
01654         }
01655       else if (op->op_flags & OP_FLAG_STORE)
01656         {
01657           add_stats (&store_can_stats, can_stats);
01658           add_stats (&store_do_stats, do_stats);
01659         }
01660       else
01661         {
01662           add_stats (&other_can_stats, can_stats);
01663           add_stats (&other_do_stats, do_stats);
01664         }
01665 
01666     }
01667 
01668   /* Print summary stats */
01669   fprintf (out,
01670            "  Category     # Ops     tries/op   opts/try  checks/try checks/opt"
01671            "\n");
01672   fprintf (out,
01673            "------------ ---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ----------"
01674            "\n");
01675   print_op_stats (out, "Jmp/Jsr/Rts", &uncond_can_stats, &uncond_do_stats);
01676   print_op_stats (out, "Cbr", &cbr_can_stats, &cbr_do_stats);
01677   print_op_stats (out, "Load", &load_can_stats, &load_do_stats);
01678   print_op_stats (out, "Store", &store_can_stats, &store_do_stats);
01679   print_op_stats (out, "Other", &other_can_stats, &other_do_stats);
01680 
01681   fprintf (out, "\n");
01682   print_op_stats (out, "Total", &total_can_stats, &total_do_stats);
01683   fprintf (out, "\n");
01684 
01685   /* Print detailed stats */
01686   /* Pull op's off heap in order and print */
01687   while ((op = (Mdes_Operation *) Heap_ExtractTop (heap)) != NULL)
01688     {
01689       if (prepass)
01690         {
01691           can_stats = &op->can_sched_prepass;
01692           do_stats = &op->sched_prepass;
01693         }
01694       else
01695         {
01696           can_stats = &op->can_sched_postpass;
01697           do_stats = &op->sched_postpass;
01698         }
01699 
01700       print_op_stats (out, op->external_name, can_stats, do_stats);
01701     }
01702 
01703   print_check_history (out, "Total", "static first choice",
01704                        total_do_stats.first_choice_dist);
01705   print_check_history (out, "Total", "static num choice",
01706                        total_do_stats.num_choice_dist);
01707 
01708   print_check_history (out, "Total", "dynamic first choice",
01709                        total_can_stats.first_choice_dist);
01710   print_check_history (out, "Total", "dynamic num choice",
01711                        total_can_stats.num_choice_dist);
01712 
01713   print_check_history (out, "Total", "succeed option check",
01714                        total_can_stats.succeed_option_check_dist);
01715   print_check_history (out, "Total", "fail option check",
01716                        total_can_stats.fail_option_check_dist);
01717   print_check_history (out, "Total", "succeed usage check",
01718                        total_can_stats.succeed_usage_check_dist);
01719   print_check_history (out, "Total", "fail usage check",
01720                        total_can_stats.fail_usage_check_dist);
01721 }
